<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Mr. Walter S. Robertson to
                        General Marshall</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d475</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">475</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Walter S. Robertson</persName> to
                        General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-25">25 May
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3111. Reference our 3054<note n="94" xml:id="d475fn94">Not found in Department
                        files.</note> you will be interested in following message, dated May 24,
                    just received from Rustemeyer, Team 11, Chengte: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Situation here greatly eased by recent statement of General
                                Marshall.<note n="95" xml:id="d475fn95">See statement to the press,
                                May 20, <ref target="#pg_865">p. 865</ref>.</note> Communist Party
                            now agree to investigate alleged violations <pb facs="0905" n="893" xml:id="pg_893"/> and to conference between representatives. Plan to
                            start on tour of the front and to effect adjustments commencing Monday
                            when all teams will be effectively constituted.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Reference appears to apply to Teams 11, 2 and 26.</p>
                <p>There has also been a marked change in personal attitude of Communists in
                    operational sections in the past few days.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
